en_221346_0	The Disaster Management centre has advised fishermen who are fishing in the Bay of Bengal to evacuate from the area and to go to a safe area immediately.
en_221346_1	The Department of Meteorology stated that the wind speed may increase up to 65 kmph from time to time in the sea areas off the coast extending from Puttalam to Mullaitivu via Kankesanthurai.
en_221346_2	The Department requests the fishing and naval community to be vigilant as the sea areas will be rough at times.
en_221346_3	Meanwhile, several spells of showers are expected in the Western, Sabaragamuwa and Southern provinces.
en_221346_4	According to the weather report thundershowers will develop after 2 pm at several places in the Eastern, Uva and Central Provinces and Polonnaruwa District.
